==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dispersive
<hw>Dis*pers"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tending to
disperse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dispersive power</b></col> <fld>(Opt.)</fld>, <cd>the
relative effect of a material in separating the different rays of light
by refraction, as when the substance is formed into a
prism.</cd></cs></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Dis*pers"ive*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disperson'ate</ent>⟦br⟧
